column8: GOTV Canvass for Cathy Myers in Kenosha!
column9:
Join us on Saturday,  August 4th at the Home of Gwendolyn Skaggs to help elect Cathy Myers! Shifts are at 10am, 12pm, 2pm, and 4pm.  We need all hands on deck (and knocking doors) as we are in the final stretch before the August 14th primary!

If you have any questions, would like to knock on doors in your neighborhood or cannot physically canvass but would like to help in another way, just let us know in the comments or email our Kenosha organizer, Krish, at krish@cathymyersforcongress.com

Cathy is a 24-year veteran high school teacher who has served on the Janesville School Board since 2013. She’s running to strengthen public education and protect our schools from gun violence by enacting commonsense gun safety reforms. She’s also a single mom who understands the struggles working families face, that’s why she’s fighting for Medicare for All so everyone has access to the healthcare they need, to guarantee affordable childcare, and to raise the minimum wage to $15 an hour. 

If you can't make it on Saturday, but would like to volunteer with Cathy Myers, email Krish@cathymyersforcongress.com or sign up here: https://cathymyersforcongress.com/volunteer-with-team-cathy/
column13: 7300 7th Ave, Kenosha, WI 53143-5556, United States -

RSVP: https://events.mobilizeamerica.io/whitmerformi/event/7401/

Rally with Gretchen to show the strength of OUR movement and then go knock doors!

Now more than ever we need to let voters know how Gretchen’s plans for healthcare, education, and infrastructure will better the lives of Michiganders. Together, we can get the vote out for Gretchen! We need all hands on deck for this final push. Bring your friends and neighbors, and sign up for as many shifts as you can! See our other events here: https://events.mobilizeamerica.io/whitmerformi/

We have four shifts on Saturday, but you can come any time if you have a few hours to give. Please consider also signing up to make calls on Election Day (find a separate sign-up for that on our events page). Election Day is our last chance to get out the vote of our supporters!

Thank you for your support of Gretchen’s campaign -- we truly can’t do this without you. Now is the time to #WinWithWhitmer. As Gretchen says, let’s get it done!

column8: Kalamazoo GOTV Canvass Event w/ Jon Hoadley & Gretchen Whitmer
column9:
We’re in the final stretch and Team Whitmer needs your help! Come knock on doors, along with special guest Representative Jon Hoadley, to share why you're supporting Gretchen!

Michigan families are counting on our leaders to make healthcare affordable, improve education, and provide a safe and clean state to grow up in. Let's get the vote out and elect a governor who won't disappoint them. Gretchen has the experience as a leader and as a mom to get the job done. We need all hands on deck for this final push, so bring your friends and neighbors!

First time knocking doors? We’ll train you! It’s fun, and having one-on-one conversations with voters is the MOST effective thing you can do to get them to the polls to support Gretchen.

Gretchen Whitmer will stop by after the canvass to thank volunteers for their hard day’s work, so come knock doors before meeting your next Governor!

Thank you for your support of Gretchen’s campaign -- we truly can’t do this without you. Now is the time to #WinWithWhitmer. As Gretchen says, let’s get it done!

lhan is the DFL endorsed candidate for the 5th Congressional District. legislator, coalition builder, organizer, and a working mom. She is the highest ranking Somali-American, Muslim woman elected to a state legislature in the United States. 

Ilhan serves as the Assistant Minority Leader at the Minnesota Legislature. As a legislator, she's championed renters rights, advocated for juvenile justice reform, expanded access to affordable childcare, and fought to protect our refugee, immigrant, and undocumented neighbors.

Ilhan has been on the cover of TIME magazine, and has won awards for her dedicated work on immigration issues, education, and advancing entrepreneurship. Earlier this year she was recognized by Governor Dayton with the MLK Service Award for her work on civil rights. She lives in the West Bank neighborhood of Minneapolis with her husband and their three children.

Join me at Optimism Brewing Company on Tuesday, August 7, for a Primary Night Party! All ages are welcome! I'll share some thoughts about the people-powered movement across the nation as we will have our eyes peeled on not only Washington’s races in the 5th, 8th, and beyond, but also on the Rashida Tlaib For Congress primary election in Michigan. 

If you’ve followed our campaign, phone-banked, knocked on doors, or donated, THANK YOU! We'll celebrate your hard-fought work that got us this far and then we'll rally to dig deep for the general election. If you’ve been looking for an opportunity to get involved, please show up, bring a friend, and sign up for a volunteer shift with our team! I am grateful for your support and committed to fighting the good fight here at home and across the nation to get our government back working for the people.

 1. Mail in your absentee ballot today - don't forget to vote for Rashida for BOTH terms!
 
 2. Vote absentee in person! Cities across the district have early voting opportunities. 
 
 - Detroit residents: 
 ---- Vote absentee in person at the Detroit Department of Elections at 2978 W. Grand Blvd in New Center, Monday through Friday, 9AM to 4PM, through election day!
 
 ---- Vote absentee in person at a satellite voting location, Monday through Friday, 9AM to 4PM, through election day! Locations:
 Wayne County Community College 
 Northwest Campus 
 8200 W. Outer Drive
 
 Wayne County Community College
 Eastern Campus
 5901 Conner
 
 3. Vote at the polls on August 7th! If you need help finding your polling place, please let us know!

column8: AZ-2: Keeping Up with the Candidates, a #YouthVote Event
column9:
All across America, young people are FIRED UP about progressive issues, and are ready to vote and take back Congress in 2018. The #youthvote is going to be critical to winning races across the country, 
 
 Join NextGen America as it hosts a fundraiser for Planned Parenthood Arizona's Southern Arizona Regional Health Center. As part of the fundraiser, the program will include a candidate debate: “Keeping Up with the Candidates.” Plus, your ticket donation gets you free food and drinks!
 
 We will eat, we will drink, and we will raise money for a good cause, all while letting primary candidates make their best case as to why you should give them your support. Just like that time 16 Republicans were on one debate stage, except not at all like that, and much more fun.

column8: Vote for Tina Smith in the Primary
column9:
Team Tina - there is a lot on the line in these midterm elections and we need you to raise your voice. Make a plan to vote for Tina in the Primary on August 14th, so we can send a message to the rest of the country that the Blue Wave is here.
 
 Tina Smith is a fierce progressive running for U.S. Senate in a special election in Minnesota. She needs your help to win this tough race, so we’re glad you're part of Team Tina!
 
 Not sure where to vote in the Primary? Find your polling place here: https://pollfinder.sos.state.mn.us/ 
 
 Not registered to vote? No problem! Register at the poll on Election Day. You can find out if you’re registered to vote here: https://mnvotes.sos.state.mn.us/VoterStatus.aspx 
 
 Learn more about Tina here: https://tinaforminnesota.com/
